ultiple-investigator projects, and must be led by personnel from a land grant institution within the 12 North Central States. Land grant graduate students and others not employed by land-grants may join a project led by an eligible land grant employee.</p>\n<p>More information:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="http://ecals.cals.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/NCRCRD_Call_for_Proposals_2013_Policy_Projects.pdf">Call for Proposals (PDF)</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://ecals.cals.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/NCRCRD_2013_Policy_Projects_Cover_Page.docx">Cover Letter (docx)</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Applications will be reviewed by the NCRCRD Board of Directors.</p>\n<p>Proposals should be received no later than <strong>September 12, 2013</strong>. Email to <a href="mailto:loverid2@msu.edu">loverid2@msu.edu</a>. Use “NCRCRD Special Project Proposal” in the subject line.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:139:"http://ecals.cals.wisc.edu/uncategorized/2013/08/15/north-central-regional-center-for-rural-development-ncrcrd-cfp-due-september-12th/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:26;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:69:"\n		\n		\n		\n 		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:15:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"New CALS faculty member JP Van Pijkeren studies bacteria-host interactions";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data"