egories are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-size: 13px;"><a href="http://leadershipwisconsin.org/other-programming/awards/leadership-excellence-awards/emerging-leader-award/">Emerging Leader</a> (under 21 years old) </span><span style="font-size: 13px;"> </span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 13px;"><a href="http://leadershipwisconsin.org/other-programming/awards/leadership-excellence-awards/modeling-the-way-award/">Modeling the Way</a> (individual) </span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 13px;"><a href="http://leadershipwisconsin.org/other-programming/awards/leadership-excellence-awards/collaborating-for-transformation-award/">Collaborating for Transformation</a> (organization) </span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size: 13px;"><a href="http://leadershipwisconsin.org/other-programming/awards/leadership-excellence-awards/collaborating-for-transformation-award/">Shaping Wisconsin Leaders</a> (leadership development program) </span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Leadership Wisconsin develops leaders and engages them in transforming their lives and communities through a variety of programs, including a 2-year leadership development program and an annual leadership conference. Leadership Excellence Awards finalists and winners will be recognized at this year’s <a href="http://conference.leadershipwisconsin.org/">Annual Leadership Conference</a> in Wisconsin Dells the evening of October 7, 2013. The conference will be held October 7 and 8, and provides leaders across the state with an opportunity to enhance their leadership skills, identify best practices and expand their network of contacts and resources. Registration for the conference is currently open and available at “conference.leadershipwisconsin.org”.</p>\n<p>For more information about the awards, annual conference or Leadership Wisconsin’s 2-year leadership development program, contact Kim Clist at 263-0817 or kimberly.clist@ces.uwex.edu.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"