urse proposal for the next two years. The committee meets again at the end of the student''s program to approve the completed coursework and sign the warrant.\r\n\r\nStudents following this track are strongly encouraged to take at least one three-credit course that provides some form of practical or real-world experience. This could include Tom Still’s LSC 640: “Issues in Science and Technology Communication,” LSC 515: "Public Communication Campaigns" or an independent study focused on practical applications relevant to the student’s overall program. Prospective students can contact <a href="mailto:kahaakenson@wisc.edu">Kristin Haakenson</a>, Student Services Coordinator, for more information.\r\n\r\n<h2>Coursework, Funding and Application</h2>\r\nA list of <a href="http://public.my.wisc.edu/portal/render.u20l1n31.target.u20l1n31.uP?pltc_target=tp.33_u20l1n31_144211&amp;pltc_type_tp.33_u20l1n31_144211=RENDER&amp;pltc_state_tp.33_u20l1n31_144211=detached&amp;pltc_mode_tp.33_u20l1n31_144211=view&amp;pltp_tp.33_u20l1n31_144211_sortOrder=CATALOG_NUMBER&amp;pltp_tp.33_u20l1n31_144211_action=advancedSearch&amp;pltp_tp.33_u20l1n31_144211_subjectChoice=120&amp;pltp_tp.33_u20l1n31_144211_alphaIndex=3&amp;pltp_tp.33_u20l1n31_144211_form-submit=true#3_Pluto_tp_33_u20l1n31_144211_" target="_blank">graduate-level courses</a> is provided in the <a title="catalog" href="http://www.wisc.edu/grad/catalog/" target="_blank">catalog</a>. To determine which classes are offered each semester and to view special topics courses and seminars, see the <a title="timetable" href="http://registrar.wisc.edu/schedule_of_classes.htm" target="_blank">timetable</a>.\r\n\r\nThe department has a limited number of project, teaching and research assistantships available. Assistantships support of one-third time or more and also provide a full tuition remission. The department nominates students with outstanding records for fellowships provided by the Graduate School. For more information on funding, <a href="http://lsc.wisc.edu/programs/graduate-studies/funding/" target="_blank">click here</a>.\r\n\r\nTo apply for either LSC Masters program, click <a href="https://www.gradsch.wisc.edu/eapp/eapp.pl" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n', 'Masters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-26 17:15:29', '2013-08-26 17:15:29', '', 29, 'http://localhost/wordpress:8888/2013/08/26/29-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(37, 44, '2013-08-26 17:43:56', '2013-08-26 17:43:56', '<p>LSC''s graduate program - a leader in professional training and scholarly communication research - is an ideal place for graduate students interested in (science) communication for many reasons, including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Graduate faculty among the <a href="http://sciencewatch.com/dr/sci/08/aug31-08_1/" target="_blank">most prolific</a> and <a title="Thomson Reuters citation data" href="http://in-cites.com/research/2007/december_3_2007-2.html" target="_blank">highly cited</a> in the world, doing cutting-edge federally funded research.</li>\r\n	<li>Exciting <a href="http://lsc.wisc.edu/research/" target="_blank">research programs</a> in core areas of communication theory and methodology, with an emphasis on the life sciences, including health, environment, technology, and energy.</li>\r\n	<li>A joint <a href="http://lsc.wisc.edu/graduate-studies/phd/" target="_blank">Ph.D. program</a> that ranks among the top two in the country in scholarly influence and graduate placement.</li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://lsc.wisc.edu/graduate-studies/degree-details/" target="_blank">Two Masters degrees</a> – either professional track or research thesis.</li>\r\n	<li>A cutting-edge teaching and research facility.</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent <a href="http://lsc.wisc.edu/graduate-studies/funding/" target="_blank">student funding</a>, including opportunities to work on federally funded centers.</li>\r\n	<li>One of the <a title="Thomson Reuters data" href="http://sciencewatch.com/inter/ins/08/08JunInsSOC/" target="_blank">most highly-ranked universities in the social sciences</a>, ahead of Columbia, Yale, Stanford, Johns Hopkins, the University of Pennsylvania, and the University of Chicago.</li>\r\n	<li>The only university, other than Johns Hopkins, that has been ranked <a href="http://badgerherald.com/news/2009/10/19/uw_cash_3rd_in_natio.php" target="_blank">in the top five research institutions</a> in terms of federal research funding for the last 20 years.</li>\r\n	<li>A <a href="http://www.uc.wisc.edu/slideshow/slideshow.html" target="_blank">perfect setting</a> in the heart of one of the great state universities in the world - a block from the blue water of Lake Mendota, surrounded by a <a href="http://www.wisc.edu/about/location.php" target="_blank">great capital city</a> (one of Kiplinger''s <a href="http://www.kiplinger.com/magazine/archives/2009/07/best-cities-2009-where-the-jobs-are.html" target="_blank">Top-10 cities of 2009</a>) with <a href="http://wistechnology.com/articles/6221/" target="_blank">one of the top health care systems in the country</a> (see <a href="https://wiscipedia.wisc.edu/index.php/Main_Page">wiscipedia.wisc.edu</a> for more information).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'Graduate', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-26 17:43:56', '2013-08-26 17:43:56', '', 18, 'http://localhost/wordpress:8888/2013/08/26/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
