(56, 44, '2013-08-27 15:13:33', '2013-08-27 15:13:33', '<h2>Alumni</h2>\r\nWe are so very proud of our alumni, who span the globe and are active in many exciting professional arenas. Overtime we have featured several alumni in our bi-annual newsletter, the <a href="http://lsc.wisc.edu/e-lsc/" target="_blank">Life Sciences Communicator</a>. Alums, please <a href="mailto:ehighland@wisc.edu">contact us</a> with any news you would like to share. Find LSC/AgJ Alumni at WAA’s <a title="UW Alumni Directory" href="http://www.uwalumni.com/" target="_blank">On-line Alumni Directory. </a>\r\n<h2><span style="color: #b5bf00">Make a gift</span></h2>\r\n<strong>LSC AND THE LSC ADVANCEMENT FUND</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Department of Life Sciences Communication serves people in Wisconsin and the larger global community by promoting effective communication regarding agriculture, the life sciences, and natural resources. In so doing, LSC embraces three core functions: undergraduate instruction, research and graduate student education, and outreach and extension.\r\n\r\nThe LSC Advancement Fund helps the department fulfill its mission by addressing the highest priorities of the department that are not funded through traditional sources. These priorities are:\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #b5bf00">| </span>Graduate student support for travel to conferences in order to present original <a href="http://lsc.wisc.edu/research/" target="_blank">research</a>; maintenance of graduate student offices so that they have necessary access to equipment.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #b5bf00">| </span>Communication with alumni and friends\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #b5bf00">| </span>Program support for issues pertaining to: food, energy, health and the environment.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in contributing a gift, please visit the <a href="http://www.supportuw.org/giving?seq=1441" target="_blank">UW Foundation Web site</a> contact <a title="Jodi Wickham" href="mailto:Jodi.Wickham@uwfoundation.wisc.edu" targ